parameters.name: domainIdentifier
parameters.description: The ID of the domain of the data product revisions that you want to list.

parameters.name: identifier
parameters.description: The ID of the data product revision.

nested_items.name: items
nested_items.description: The results of the ListDataProductRevisions action.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The timestamp at which the data product revision was created.

nested_items.name: createdBy
nested_items.description: The user who created the data product revision.

nested_items.name: domainId
nested_items.description: The ID of the domain where the data product revision lives.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: The ID of the data product revision.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: When the number of data product revisions is greater than the default value for the MaxResults parameter, or if you explicitly specify a value for MaxResults that is less than the number of data product revisions, the response includes a pagination token named NextToken. You can specify this NextToken value in a subsequent call to ListDataProductRevisions to list the next set of data product revisions.
